BungieNet.Engine.Contract.Destiny.World..description: Tess Everis is an accomplished broker of stylish and highly coveted items procured from the City and beyond.

interactions.flavorLineOne:
Tess welcomes you warmly, as always, then leans a little closer to you. "If you wouldn't mind me asking a favor…"

She presents you with a bounty note. "Hard to get away from the shop, I'm afraid. If it's too much trouble, don't worry about it."
Tess smiles. "Ah, perfect. Thank you so much. Here, take this." She offers you a Bright Engram. "It's the least I can do."
Tess welcomes you to her stall, handing you a gift that will help you usher in the new season in style.

headerDisplayProperties.name: Welcome to the Solstice of Heroes

interactions.flavorLineOne: Tess greets you warmly as you approach—and gives you a gift to celebrate the Solstice of Heroes.

You're no closer to knowing whether the rumor Tess heard was real or not.

Undaunted, she presents you with a Jubilant Gift. "Make the most of the Revelry, Guardian."
Tess seems a bit glum to not receive any treats herself, but she still rewards you with a gift from Eververse's Dawning collection.
Tess smiles. "I have something for you, Guardian. No need for repayment. Here—I hope it spurs the imagination."
You receive a package with a note from Tess that reads: "I have something for you, Guardian. No need for repayment. Here—I hope it spurs the imagination."
Tess greets you with a warm smile. "I hope you're enjoying the nice weather, Guardian."
"I hope the Solstice is everything you want it to be," Tess says. She hands you a Bright Engram with a smile, then turns toward her next customer.
Tess smiles. "I have something for you, Guardian. No need for repayment. Here—I hope it spurs the imagination."

"Ah, the Revelry!" Tess says. "What a good tradition for us to embrace."

She pauses, then asks, "Is it true that someone hacked the Infinite Forest to simulate something a bit more… cheerful? I heard maybe Sagira complained to Osiris. Ha! Wouldn't that be rich. But maybe you could follow up on those rumors for me. Do you mind?"
A Cryptarch can decrypt complex engrams into powerful gear and other items.
